      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "| SAN FRANCISCO, Nov. 1.-THE\nBunker Hill & Sullivan Co. defeat\nJed the farmers of the Occur\nkd'Alene River valley in their fight\n\n\nto enjoin the mining company from\npoisoning the water with mining\nIsilts from the mills. The court of\nappeals upheld the decision of the\nIdaho court in refusing an injunc-\n\n\nton. The farmers represented\n\n\n100000 worth of property and the\nmining company $12,000,000.\n\\ The suits of Timothy Mccarthy,\n\n\nWilliam Raney and Elmer Doty are\nwithout prejudice, which\n\n\ngives them a chance to sue again\nIF they want to."
    }
